Whereas only 22 percent of Americans report regular, sustained physical activity and only 5 percent
			 of adults achieve the recommended 150 minutes per week of moderate to
			 vigorous physical activity;

Whereas sedentary lifestyles increase the likelihood of chronic diseases, including diabetes, which
			 accounts for more than $98,000,000,000 in direct and indirect medical
